arts.ttl: Fleetwood Town v Cheltenham Town RECAP: Robins' away struggles continue
arts.sum: With Cheltenham chasing an equaliser and committing players forward in the final moments, the home side added a second in the second minute of time added on at the end of the 90, with substitute Mark Helm racing from inside his own half on a through ball from Bonds and slotting low past Joe Day. Matty Virtue, who netted both goals in Fleetwood's 2-0 win at Whaddon Road earlier in the season, opened the scoring in the 44th minute after good work in the box from Elliot Bonds.

arts.ttl: Fleetwood see off Cheltenham to get back to winning ways
arts.sum: Matty Virtue and Mark Helm struck for the home side.

arts.ttl: Proud of players, Tommy Backwell injury blow and positive impact from Tim Dieng - Cheltenham Town boss Michael Flynn after Peterborough United defeat
arts.sum: Those are the goals he thrives on, going through, playing on the shoulder of defenders and it was a great finish, lift of the ball. Two really good goals scored, Jordan Thomas with a lovely finish
